<TEXT>
   The Senate panel studying the blast aboard the
USS Iowa that killed 47 sailors last April will hear testimony next
Monday from the skipper of the battleship.
   Capt. Fred P. Moosally will answer questions at the panel's
second hearing, it was announced Monday. The committee heard
testimony last month from Rear Adm. Richard Milligan, who oversaw
the Navy's technical and criminal investigation of the blast.
   The Navy concluded in its Sept. 7 report that gunner's mate
Clayton Hartwig ``most likely'' caused the explosion by inserting
some type of detonator between bags of gunpowder in one of the
ship's 16-inch guns. Hartwig was among those killed.
   Milligan told the committee that additional technical tests
conducted since the report found ``unique foreign material'' that
would not have been present during a normal firing.
