<FIRST>r a PM-BargeExplosion     12-05 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Barge Explosion,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>One Missing, One Injured In Houston Ship Channel Barge Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fuel barge exploded in the Houston Ship
Channel, injuring one man and leaving another missing, authorities
said.
   The injured man was transported to a local hospital suffering
from burns after the explosion Monday afternoon, said Cpl. Rodney
Tooley with the Harris County Sheriff's Department. He was in
guarded but stable condition Monday night at Hermann Hospital.
   The search for the missing man was called off later because of
darkness. Coast Guard officials were not sure if the search would
resume today.
   Houston Fire Department boats and a sheriff's marine division
boat helped douse the fire on the barge. The initial explosion sent
up thick black smoke that was visible from downtown Houston, about
20 miles away.
   U.S. Coast Guard officials said the injured and missing men were
part of a crew cleaning the barge, which had been carrying a form
of natural gas when the explosion occurred.
</TEXT>
