<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--SexStudy     12-05 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Sex Study,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>Michigan Study: Most Women Have Had At Least 3 Sex Partners by Age
35</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fewer than one in 10 Michigan woman surveyed as
part of a nationwide study said they have had only one sex partner
by age 35, while 81 percent said they had sex with three or more.
   About 14 percent of the women surveyed by Dr. Richard Reid, a
Southfield gynecologist, said they had 13 or more sex partners by
age 35.
   Reid surveyed 962 women between ages 18 and 35 in Detroit,
Kalamazoo, Southfield and Berkley as part of a U.S. Centers for
Disease Control study on detecting a virus that has been linked to
cancer of the cervix.
   The survey showed 9 percent of the Michigan women have had one
sex partner by age 35; 9.6 percent had two; nearly half had three
to seven; and nearly 19 percent had eight to 12 partners. Of the 14
percent reporting 13 or more sex partners by age 35, nearly half
said they had sex with 25 or more partners.
