   Radicals who oppose expansion of Narita Airport
today hurled firebombs and bricks at police who fought back with
water cannon. One protester was arrested for blocking construction
work.
   About 5,000 riot police officers continued work begun Monday to
remove one of 10 huts built illegally on the site for a second
runway at the airport, 40 miles northeast of Tokyo.
   Yoshikazu Kawakami, 22, a member of the Battle Flag radical
leftist group, was arrested for defying a court injunction and
