firebombs and bricks at police this morning, officials said. Police
fired water cannon and used cranes to lower steel cages onto the
towers to contain the hurled objects.
   Farmers and their supporters, including radicals seizing on the
issue for their anti-government activities, have been resisting the
government's plans to expropriate farmland to build the $2.5
billion runway.
   Pressure to complete the 8,250-foot runway is growing as
complaints of air-traffic congestion mount. The government hopes to
complete construction next year.
