<HEAD>Santa Claus Character Robs Bank</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST CHESTER, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man wearing a Santa Claus suit sang
``We Wish You a Merry Christmas'' as he held up a bank, dashing
away with an undetermined amount of money.
   ``You always see Santa Claus walking around this time of year,''
West Goshen Township police Officer Richard Geiger said. ``No one
thinks anything of it. If it happened in July, that would be a
different story.''
   Geiger said the pseudo-Santa entered a Fidelity Bank branch
Monday afternoon, waited in line with other customers, then told
the teller he was there to present a singing telegram.
   The robber then handed the teller a red plastic bag with
drawstrings and pictures of Santa. His note instructed the teller
to place cash in the bag until he was finished with his song,
police said.
   Geiger said the amount of money taken had not been determined.
