<HEAD>Bush Nominates Puerto Rican Health Official to Defense Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Tuesday he will nominate
Dr. Enrique Mendez Jr., Puerto Rico's secretary of health, to be
assistant secretary of defense for health affairs.
   Mendez, 58, is a retired Army major general and former deputy
surgeon general of the Army and commander of Walter Reed Army
Medical Center.
   After retiring from the Army in 1983, he became dean of the
Ponce School of Medicine in his native Puerto Rico. He became the
commonwealth's secretary of health earlier this year.
   Mendez would succeed Dr. William E. Mayer in the post, which
requires Senate confirmation.
   Mendez, a graduate of the University of Puerto Rico and Loyola
University Medical School in Chicago, lives in Caparra Heights, P.R.
