<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--Newton     12-05 0104</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Newton,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Robinson Pleads Innocent In Huey Newton Killing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tyrone Robinson, accused of the Aug. 22
curbside killing of Black Panther Party co-founder Huey P. Newton,
pleaded innocent Tuesday in Alameda County Superior Court.
   Judge Gordon Baranco ordered the 25-year-old defendant to trial
on Jan. 24, and granted a bail hearing for Dec. 14. Robinson has
been held without bail since the dawn shooting that took the life
of the charismatic black leader of the 1960s.
   The prosecution contends Robinson shot Newton to improve his
standing with the Black Guerrilla prison gang. Robinson says he
shot Newton in self-defense.
</TEXT>
