<HEAD>Inmate Tries to Escape in Fire Truck, Authorities Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRONTERA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convicted killer drove a fire truck in
an attempt to escape prison, ramming fences, gates and other
vehicles during a rampage that ended when she crashed into a tree.
   Shirley Wolf, 20, will ``very likely be charged with attempted
escape with force,'' said Ross Dykes, associate warden at the
California Institution for Women.
   Wolf, sentenced at 14 for the first-degree stabbing murder of an
85-year-old woman, apparently scaled an inner fence at the prison
to get to the fire truck Monday night, officials said.
   ``She started a one-ton fire truck and began driving erratically
from the fire station, striking several other maintenance
vehicles,'' Dykes said. Wolf then drove through a gate.
   ``Wolf then used the truck to ram a narrow fenced entry to get
into a yard area. Unsuccessful, she accelerated rapidly in reverse
and struck a tree. We then placed the inmate under control,'' he
said.
