<FIRST>r w AM-NevadaWilderness     12-05 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Nevada Wilderness,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>President Signs Bill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Tuesday signed legislation
creating 733,400 acres of protected wilderness in Nevada and
opening an additional 2.4 million acres to multiple use under the
management of the Agriculture Department.
   The measure creates 13 new wilderness areas within Nevada and
adds to one other existing area. That would put a total of 2
percent of the state's land under wildernss protection, preventing
development and such uses as timber harvesting, mineral exploration
or intrusion by campers in vehicles.
   However, the legislation protects existing grazing rights for
ranchers on the wilderness land, and low-level military flights
over four of the new wilderness areas, said White House spokesman
Steve Hart.
