<HEAD>US West, Hungarian Organization to Develop Cellular System</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: With PM-Lin-McCaw, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   US West Inc. and the Hungarian
government phone company have signed an agreement to operate a
cellular telephone system in Hungary, the first in Eastern Europe,
the company said.
   Construction is expected to start in the second quarter of 1990,
with initial service being offered in Budapest in the first quarter
of 1991, US West and Magyar Posta announced Monday. The first phase
of the project will cost about $10 million.
   US West said the system eventually will provide mobile cellular
communications throughout Hungary, which has a population of 10.6
million people.
   US West is one of the seven regional Bell phone companies.
