<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0319</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was higher in moderate trading
today after a weak start.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 5.54 points to
2,759.17 at 10 a.m. EST, 30 minutes after the opening bell.
   Advancing issues outpaced decliners by about 4 to 3 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 560 issues up, 421 down and 543 unchanged.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board totaled 22.88 million
shares.
   Analysts said after opening on the negative side the market got
a lift from IBM's announcement of a massive restructuring,
including a $4 billion share buyback.
   ``The market was down and it bounced back after the IBM
announcement,'' said Brad Weeks, head of equity trading for
Donaldson, Lufkin &amp; Jenrette.
   Strength in UAL stock also was helping pull the transportation
sector higher, analysts said.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.22 to 194.29.
   The American Stock Exchange market value index was unchanged at
374.66.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, UAL was up 5 to 184{
after a 5\-point gain on Monday. Strength in the stock followed
news that investment group Condor Partners has raised its stake in
UAL to 11.8 percent and is holding talks with the company and its
major unions.
   Trading in IBM stock was delayed after the announcement.
   USX was up \ to 38, McDonalds had advanced [ to 33~ and Reebok
had gained [ to 18.
   On Monday, the Dow Jones industrial average advanced 5.98 points
to 2,753.63.
   Advancing issues edged out decliners by about 8 to 7 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 810 issues up, 708 down and 469 unchanged.
   Big Board volume totaled 150.36 million shares, down from 199.20
million in Friday's session.
