<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell in afternoon trading,
reflecting investor confusion about the direction of the economy,
analysts said.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down 7.26 points to
2,746.37 at 2 p.m. EST. The blue-chip indicator was up 4.05 points
at noon.
   Declining issues outpaced advancers by about 5 to 4 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 789 issues down, 632 up and 512 unchanged.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 115.32 million
