retreated shortly after midday.
   ``We have a very dull and down drifting market,'' said Alfred E.
Goldman, vice president of A.G. Edwards &amp; Sons Inc. in St Louis.
   Wall Street analysts said the economy and interest rates
continued to be the focal point of concern ahead of Friday's report
on November unemployment. Most recent economic data has pointed to
a slowdown in economic growth.
